http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/%E2%80%98Support-cause-of-Telugu-in-Malaysia%E2%80%99/article14019231.ece

Working tirelessly for promotion of Telugu language and culture in the country which lakhs made their home, Telugu Association of Malaysia seeks the governments’ support in furthering the cause of language and bringing them closer to Andhra Pradesh.Association president Datuk Dr. Achaiah Kumar Rao urged the governments of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana to provide them teachers to help foster the language.“We want teachers to help our children learn Telugu. We need a total of 40 teachers and 10 to begin with and the association will bear all the expenses,” he told reporters here on Sunday.We want teachers to help our children learn Telugu. We need a total of 40 teachers and 10 to begin with and the association will bear all the expensesDatuk Dr. Achaiah Kumar RaoPresident, Telugu Association of Malaysia